      "Here we go with Old Western #1.  Of course, this happens to be the longest movie on the watchlist, clocking in at almost three and a half hours (!).  I like epic movies sometimes, but I was hoping to ease into the longer ones this watchlist.  But it’s all right, I liked the movie.  It really felt like<strong> Gone With the Wind (1939)</strong> but with a Texas ranch as the backdrop.. and also the main characters don’t seem to hate each other so much.  Like Gone With the Wind, time passes pretty quick in the movie.. from just meeting each other, to getting married, to having kids, the kids growing, etc.  While it is a Western in the geographical sense, it really doesn’t “feel” much like a classic western.  It’s more like 1920-1950 range.. cars, planes, all that.  Even though it wasn’t quite what I expected of a western, the movie was still entertaining throughout and it was nice to see a relationship that’s a little more realistic and not too sugar-coated.  Also, this is the first James Dean movie I’ve watched and his character was.. ok.  I felt like he could have been fleshed out more.  All in all though, good movie and a good option for one of those old Hollywood epics.",
