      "Some comedy horror movies hook me in right from the start, like <strong>Zombieland (2009)</strong> and to a degree <strong>Deathgasm (2015)</strong>.  Those are two movies I think of as my “standard” for modern comedy horrors.  With The Editor, it took some time for me to start to “get” it.. it can be a little goofy, but not in a cringey way.  But mid-way through, I started to get it.. seeing homages to other horror movies was part of what sold me.  One homage to <strong>The New York Ripper (1982)</strong> stood out because it’s like.. how many people watching this also have seen The New York Ripper to get this reference?  Also, the whole giallo aspect of the movie is great, especially having watched a few these past weeks.  The fake movie, the fake movie posters, the purposely awkward dialogue sometimes.. it’s really directed at weirdos like me.  I started out thinking the movie was “eh” but as it went along, I was more and more on board.  Even though a lot of the comedy was just the exhale-a-burst-of-air-out-of-my-nose type “laughs” and not laugh-out-loud, I still enjoyed the subtlety of some of the comedy.",
