      "I don’t have a good opening line here so I’ll just say: this movie was good.  I’ve been more and more pleasantly surprised with Larry Fessenden movies.  I originally bought the Scream Factory set as more of a completionist thing, but now I’m glad I did.  So far, every movie on there has been at least “pretty good” in my book, and this one was even better.  It’s actually a very “quiet” movie (slow, but not boring), but it hits a lot of the things I like: snow, isolation, small town vibe and subtlety.  The cast is good (cmon, Dewey from Malcolm in the Middle!) and everything is played out in a really subdued, realistic way.  The premise is simple.. a family with one kid is on their way to some snowy retreat when they hit a deer in the road which was being hunted and one of the hunter is kind of pissed off about it.  From there, it’s more drama than horror, but for someone who isn’t expecting a monster fest (the title IS Wendigo..) and can accept something slower paced, it’s pretty great",
