      "Well… this is an interesting watch in 2021.  The maniacs here are a bunch of Confederate-flag-waving southerners who lure a group of victims into their small town to kill them in elaborate and bloody ways.  They do this as some kind of 100 year anniversary/ritual related to the end of the US Civil War.  Maybe a sequel in 2065..?  Despite its cheap appearance, it’s actually not a bad movie.  Of course, being an HG Lewis movie, it’s gorey, especially for the early part of the 1960s.  The maniacs were pretty creepy in their own way, “friendly” the whole time.  It’s a movie worth watching even almost 60 years later.. I think the idea of being lured into a group of crazies is always a scary premise (like <strong>The Hills Have Eyes (1977)</strong> for example), so this holds up in that way.",
