      "I couldn’t quite get past the fact that the main character is Lloyd Braun from Seinfeld (bonus: Jackie Chiles is also in the movie).  I’d chuckle once in a while just watching this guy, thinking about him in Seinfeld.  Anyway, trying to get past that.. the movie is ok.  I would say it’s not <em>good</em>.. but I would take a monster movie over another supernatural ghost movie any day.  The monster is I guess supposed to be the abominable snowman creature?  Though, it’s really more like bigfoot and I don’t recall there being any snow.. Lloyd Braun is a guy who is wheelchair-bound and watches a group of vacationing girls through the window.  Basically, take <strong>Rear Window (1954)</strong> but with Lloyd Braun, add the girls trip element of <strong>The Descent (2005)</strong>, but if the girls were more annoying and worse actresses and add in a bigfoot type creature and basically that’s the movie.  There are also a couple really small roles for some horror icons.. Dee Wallace, Jeffrey Combs and Lance Henriksen, so it definitely seems like it’s made by horror fans and not just a cheap cash-in.  So I give it points for the heart and the charm of a more modern-day creature movie, but overall, it’s not really a particularly good movie… but it’s fun.",
