      "Starting the “randomizer” watchlist with a Stephen King adaptation.  This might have fit into my “Stephen King Non-Horror” theme from a few weeks ago since it’s not really horror, more of a suspense.  This is one of those rare cases where I had actually already read the source material before seeing the movie and I think that kind of hinders the viewing experience.  The premise is an interesting one and the cast is pretty decent, but it’s not really a story that needs to be a full-length movie.  I’m sure I’ve complained about this several times in other Stephen King short story adaptations but.. I’m doing it again anyway.  It’s an easy enough watch though and they didn’t do anything too egregious with the adaptation.  I was worried that it would have some younger married couple as the main characters to appeal to a younger audience, which would kind of ruin the whole point of the story.. but luckily, they stuck to the story.  It’s ok but I think I would forget ever having seen it if it wasn’t attached to Stephen King’s name.",
