      "The new theme on the block: Arrow Crime.  I have a lot of movies released by Arrow films since they specialize in 70s/80s horror and action.  Right up my alley, but that means I have a big backlog to get through.  So this theme will help me get through three of them.  The first one, <strong>Cruising</strong>, is one I’d never heard of until Arrow released it.  I can kind of see why it didn’t become a big classic given it’s focus around a controversial community.. the heavy leather and S&amp;M gay scene.  These guys are wild!  I don’t know if these clubs are like that in real life but man.. it’s wild.  Anyway, the movie is a murder mystery within that scene with Al Pacino as an undercover cop.  It’s a good movie but I felt like some things were missing and, based on what I read after, that’s true.  Sounds like a lot of footage had to be cut and permanently destroyed.  Despite Pacino being the main character and having plenty of screen-time, I felt like it might have been nice to “know” his character more.  Anyway, the movie could have been better with extra footage to make some things make a bit more sense, but even still, it was pretty good.  My favorite part was the interrogation “intimidator”.. or whatever he was.  “Who is that guy??”",
