      "Here we are.. the final week, and it’s Vincent Price time.  After collecting some Vincent Price Scream Factory collections as well as other various movies of his, it made a lot of sense to dedicate a week of just catching up on some of those movies.  I chose it because, of all the themes, I think Vincent Price exudes the most Halloween atmosphere.  After all, he did the monologue for Thriller..   Thriller.  Anyway, the first movie, <strong>House of Wax</strong>, is pretty good.  I already knew the basic plot and finale, so maybe it had less of an impact than it otherwise could have.  I imagine this was pretty shocking and dark for 1953.  If only I had a 3D TV to see this in full effect, but sadly, I watched it in 2D.  Anyway, I liked this movie.. it has a legitimately creepy premise and of course Vincent Price sells it.",
