      "Stepping out of the 70s this time to an 80s movie made by one of the primary Italian filmmakers, Dario Argento.  It definitely feels like a different decade than the previous movies this week, especially with the awesome soundtrack.. but in other ways, it still has that Italian mystery feel.  Maybe partially due to the “new girl arriving at a European school” premise that <strong>Suspiria (1977)</strong> has.  I could have used a little more Donald Pleasance, but at least his monkey came through in the clutch.  I enjoyed this one most of the time, though it dragged a little for me early in the third act but the wild ending made up for that.",
