      "<li>Ranking: Phenomena, The Bloodstained Butterfly, Your Vice is a Locked Room and Only I Have the Key, Beyond the Door, All the Colors of the Dark</li><li>All of these movies were roughly a similar rating for me, none of them bad.  Of all the Italian/giallo movies I’ve seen, they usually at least seem to be well-made and good on the atmosphere.. it’s just a matter of whether the plot and characters draw me in</li><li>In retrospect, maybe it would have been fun to do this theme first, then 80s slashers, since 80s slashers are kind of a descendant of giallos</li>",
      "I’ve got bonus movies up my sleeve and then it’s on to the final week, which is sad.  But I’m definitely going to continue to do more movie watchlists throughout the year (not always horror) because I find it super fun and I (you, Future Me) will enjoy coming back and reading my initial thoughts on all these movies sometime down the line.  Also, instead of standing there paralyzed for 20 minutes looking at my movies trying to decide which one to watch and then ultimately just re-watching a movie I’ve seen many times, this forces me to work through my backlog of unseen but owned movies.  Instead of deliberating “is this really the movie I want to watch right now?”, I just look at the watchlist and say “this is the next one, let’s do it” and that’s very freeing.  Freed from the tyranny of too may blu-rays.",
