      "Hey, it wasn’t as bad as I thought.  Going into it, I expected it to be pretty rough.. and to be fair, some of the quality had to be because, according to a note at the beginning of this restoration, they didn’t have raw footage to restore, so they could only try to clean up old VHS footage.  They said they felt they needed to restore those scenes for a “film of this importance”.. anyway, it’s kind of fun to watch it that way, to see a 5-10 second segment of VHS quality video then back to HD, it makes you appreciate how far we’ve come with our technology.",
