      "https://einysrentals.files.wordpress.com/2020/09/00100lrportrait_00100_burst20200921221258349_cover.jpg?w=800&h=600&crop=1",
    content: [
      "Let me first say that I have higher-than-average tolerance for bad horror movies from the 70s through the 90s.  I attribute it to watching Mystery Science Theater 3000 while growing up and trying to rent the funniest bad movies my friends and I could find at the video rental store in high school.  This movie.. is not a good movie.  But it has a <em>little</em> bit of that MST3K comfort food feeling, so I don’t feel too bad afterwards.  I don’t even know how the beginning of the movie relates to any of the rest and I really didn’t expect it to be like this “land of the lost” kind of movie with tribal people on a foreign planet fighting each other in different colored filters.  But the point is to entertain and it mostly did. I particularly liked those little bad dudes flying from the cave walls.  Anyway, I never really know how to “assess” these bad movies.  Objectively it’s like a 2/10, but when they have a bit of heart and fun to them, I give them some credit.  After all, it’s just a movie..",
      "4/10",
    ],
    title: "#24 – Week 4 – Movie 2 – Horror of the Blood Monsters (1970)",
